Episodes.Title: Dance Like Nobody's Watching
Episodes.Plot: Tracy becomes frustrated in his attempts to anger Liz. Jack questions the family value of the network's new talent competition and Kenneth awaits the Rapture.
Episodes.GuestStars: John McEnroe

Episodes.Title: Idiots are People Two!
Episodes.Plot: An offensive rant by Tracy is leaked online. Jack disapproves of Liz's new boyfriend, and the Best Friends Gang is reunited when Kenneth and Jenna call for the help of Kelsey Grammer.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kelsey Grammer, Denise Richards, Ann Curry, James Marsden

Episodes.Title: Idiots are People Three!
Episodes.Plot: Tracy Jordan challenges Liz by leading his own protest in defense of idiots everywhere. Jack faces off with Devin Banks yet again, but still finds time to interfere with Liz's relationship by giving Criss an ultimatum, and Liz tries to get rid of Jenna's new assistant.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kelsey Grammer, Denise Richards, Marceline Hugot, James Marsden, Will Arnett

Episodes.Title: The Ballad of Kenneth Parcell
Episodes.Plot: Liz looks for a new best friend after discovering that Jenna has traded their friendship for fame. Tracy contemplates mortality as Dotcom and Grizz scramble to show him that life is still worth living. Meanwhile, Jack decides to end the page program in order to impress Hank Hooper.
Episodes.GuestStars: Ken Howard, Andy Samberg, Emma Stone, Nick Cannon, Mick Foley, Julie Dretzin, Steve Earle

Episodes.Title: Today You Are a Man
Episodes.Plot: Jack and Liz battle over her employment contract. Kenneth is reassigned after being offended by his coworkers at TGS, and Tracy and Jenna's accountant hires them as entertainment at a bar mitzvah.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kristen Schaal, Suze Orman

Episodes.Title: Hey, Baby, What's Wrong? (1)
Episodes.Plot: Criss and Liz decide to celebrate Valentine's Day, but they need to buy a dining room table first. Jack entertains his mother-in-law, Diana, as Jenna frantically looks to Pete to fill in last-minute as the producer of her first live performance on "America's Kidz Got Singing." Back at the office, Tracy and Frank try to help Lutz find someone to spend Valentine's with.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Dean Winters, Mary Steenburgen, Kristen Schaal, Chris Parnell, Billy Bush, Erik Jensen

Episodes.Title: Hey, Baby, What's Wrong? (2)
Episodes.Plot: Criss and Liz decide to celebrate Valentine's Day, but they need to buy a dining room table first. Jack entertains his mother-in-law, Diana, as Jenna frantically looks to Pete to fill in last-minute as the producer of her first live performance on "America's Kidz Got Singing." Back at the office, Tracy and Frank try to help Lutz find someone to spend Valentine's with.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Dean Winters, Mary Steenburgen, Kristen Schaal, Chris Parnell, Billy Bush, Erik Jensen

Episodes.Title: The Tuxedo Begins
Episodes.Plot: Fed up with New York City after being mugged, Jack sets out to protect the safety of the city's elite by announcing his run for mayor. Meanwhile, Liz revels in sacrificing the good of the city to look out for her own interests, and Jenna and Paul are thrilled by the perversion of acting like a normal couple.
Episodes.GuestStars: Will Forte, Steve Buscemi

Episodes.Title: Leap Day
Episodes.Plot: Jack learns to appreciate Leap Day while Tracy takes the writers to a restaurant to spend an almost-expired gift card. Liz helps Jenna seduce a billionaire online.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Andie MacDowell, Jim Carrey, Adriane Lenox, Steve Little, John Cullum, Karolina Kurkova, Nicol Paone

Episodes.Title: Alexis Goodlooking and the Case of the Missing Whisky
Episodes.Plot: In order to hide his relationship with Lynn, Frank convinces his mother that he is dating Liz. Tracy and Jenna team up to try to solve the case of Pete's missing whisky. Meanwhile, Jack teaches Kenneth how to take down his first business nemesis.
Episodes.GuestStars: Stanley Tucci, Patti LuPone, Susan Sarandon

Episodes.Title: Standards and Practices
Episodes.Plot: Jenna hatches a surprising new plan to get publicity, while Jack finds himself begrudgingly playing parent to his teenage nemesis, Kaylie Hooper. Liz rejects the new authority Kenneth has over ?TGS? with his new job in Standards.
Episodes.GuestStars: Chloë Grace Moretz, Ken Howard, Thomas Roberts, Carly Tamer

Episodes.Title: St. Patrick's Day
Episodes.Plot: Jack feels unworthy of his latest award and attempts to redeem himself by taking on the writers in a strategic board game. Liz believes she's cursed on St. Patrick's Day when her ex-boyfriend Dennis shows up to derail her relationship with Criss. Meanwhile, Hazel struggles to keep the peace between Tracy and Jenna.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Dean Winters, Kristen Schaal, Al Roker, Bernie McInerney, Ira Glass, Sue Galloway

Episodes.Title: Grandmentor
Episodes.Plot: Liz struggles in her new role as mentor to Hazel. Kenneth has a difficult time letting go of his page duties and takes drastic measures to make sure Tracy is taken care of. Meanwhile, Jack and Jenna come up with a plan to get Avery back in the headlines.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kristen Schaal, Matt Lauer

Episodes.Title: Kidnapped by Danger
Episodes.Plot: Liz's scripted version of Jack and Avery's love story leaves Jack confused and frustrated by his feelings for Diana. Meanwhile, Jenna and Tracy attempt to beat Weird Al Yankovic at his own game, and Kenneth gets an unexpected new job at NBC.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mary Steenburgen, Cynthia Nixon, Jimmy Fallon, Weird Al Yankovic, William Baldwin, Seth Kirschner, Chiquinquirá Delgado

Episodes.Title: The Shower Principle
Episodes.Plot: A curse strikes TGS. Liz dares to be different after realizing that the same things happen every year, and Jack vows to wow Hank Hooper.
Episodes.GuestStars: Kristen Schaal, Thomas Roberts, Ken Howard

Episodes.Title: Nothing Left to Lose
Episodes.Plot: Tracy regains his sense of smell and finds an unusual father figure in Liz, while the writers spark a prank war with Jenna.
Episodes.GuestStars: Grizz Chapman, Richard Prioleau

Episodes.Title: Meet the Woggels
Episodes.Plot: Jack's mom upstages his ribbon-cutting ceremony. Meanwhile Jenna hooks up with a "rock star" and Tracy frets about his son heading to college.
Episodes.GuestStars: Elaine Stritch, Will Forte

Episodes.Title: Murphy Brown Lied to Us
Episodes.Plot: Jack sets Liz up on a blind date to show her what she's missing in her relationship with Criss. Meanwhile at KableTown, Jack has to scramble when his plan to manufacture couches hits a speed bump. With Tracy's help, Jenna orchestrates a public meltdown to get Paul's attention.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Stacy Keach, Will Forte, Bobby Moynihan, Matt Lauer, Vinny Anand, Tom McNutt, Bebe Wood, Curt Bouril, Stephen Beach, Paul Juhn, Steven Hauck, Kelly Deadmon, Dhruvi Patel

Episodes.Title: Live from Studio 6H (East Coast)
Episodes.Plot:
Kabletown chooses to stop funding live shows for TGS. While Liz and Jack embrace the change, Kenneth argues that live format should be kept intact, and he tries to convince the TGS staff to fight for their right to be live by taking them and our audience through a magical look back at the illustrious history of Studio 6H.

The episode was filmed twice.  The East Coast version aired for the Eastern, Central and Mountain time zones. The West Coast version was aired in the western, Alaskan and Hawa
Episodes.GuestStars: Fred Armisen, Jimmy Fallon, Will Forte, Donald Glover, Jon Hamm, Paul McCartney, Chris Parnell, Amy Poehler, Kristen Schaal, Brian Williams

Episodes.Title: Queen of Jordan II: Mystery of the Phantom Pooper
Episodes.Plot: Angie brings "Queen of Jordan'' back to TGS. News about Avery forces Jack to confront his feelings for her mother, and Liz finds herself in a feud.
Episodes.GuestStars: Mary Steenburgen, Tituss Burgess, Sherri Shepherd

Episodes.Title: The Return of Avery Jessup
Episodes.Plot: Avery finally returns home from her kidnapping ordeal in North Korea, yet Jack grows uncertain of her fidelity while she was away. Elsewhere, Criss is crossed due to Liz's role as top wage earner, and Jenna seeks a sponsor for her approaching nuptials.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Margaret Cho, Michael Mosley, Elizabeth Banks

Episodes.Title: What Will Happen to the Gang Next Year?
Episodes.Plot: Determined to prove his marriage has survived Avery's kidnapping unscathed, Jack asks Liz to officiate their vow renewal. Meanwhile, Criss (Marsden) tries to convince Liz that he's worth sticking around for. Tracy meets with Cornel West to discuss his influence as a black celebrity.
Episodes.GuestStars: James Marsden, Mary Steenburgen, Margaret Cho, Kristen Schaal, Michael Mosley, Thomas Roberts, Cornel West, Pat Kiernan, Elizabeth Banks
